Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of kernel distance for shapes, which suggests a connection to computational geometry and topology, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. The mention of an RKHS (Reproducing Kernel Hilbert Space) suggests a connection to functional analysis, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the mathematical underpinnings of the kernel distance, which suggests a connection to numerical analysis, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible sub-category.
